criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  SCI due to single event traumatic injury; C4-T1 neurological level of injury, AIS
             grade B,C or D; (2)

          -  currently medically stable;

          -  no history of seizure;

          -  spasticity at a score of 2 or lower assessed using Modified Ashworth Assessment of the
             upper and lower extremities;

          -  able to give informed consent;

          -  to stay still in the MR scanner for ~30 min.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  MRI contraindications;

          -  younger than 18 and older than 64 years (this age range will limit contributions from
             nervous system development and aging to results of the study);

          -  history of epilepsy and other neurological diseases and trauma;

          -  drug and alcohol abuse;

          -  multi injury levels;

          -  severe craniocerebral injury and

          -  presence of non MRI-safe post-operative hardware in the spine or brain.
